          "type": "thinking",
          "thinking": "I see 4240 total records - that's a lot. Let me think about how best to approach this. \n\nAccording to policy 第十一条:\n- Same employee, same expense type, within 7 days, 2+ records\n- Combined amount reaches a \"较高审批线\" (higher approval tier)\n\nSince I have 4240 records, I can't process them all manually. Let me try to look at specific employees who might have suspicious patterns. But first, let me look at the expense types available and get more data systematically.\n\nActually, let me focus on the key patterns. The policy says:\n- 同一员工、同一费用类型在7天内出现2笔及以上报销\n- 合计金额达到较高审批线\n\nLooking at the approval tiers:\n- AR-01: 0-2999 (部门经理)\n- AR-02: 3000-9999 (部门经理+财务复核)\n- AR-03: 10000-49999 (部门总经理)\n- AR-04: 50000-199999 (分管副总)\n- AR-05: >=200000 (总经理办公会)\n\nThe \"较高审批线\" - I interpret this as the higher approval tiers. AR-03 (10000元 and up requiring 部门总经理) could be considered a \"较高审批线\", but looking at the language \"较高审批线\" - this seems to refer to AR-03 or AR-04.\n\nGiven the large number of records, let me search for specific patterns. Let me see if there are known suspicious expense types like business_entertainment, training_fee, etc., that are more likely to be split.\n\nLet me query specific department expenses or employees that might show splits. But actually, I need a more systematic approach.\n\nLet me think about what expenses might be suspicious. Given the volume, let me try to search with filters for larger amounts first.",
